                <head>No. 984.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Curry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 276.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 304 of the 3d instant, inclosing copy of
                    the royal decree providing for an exposition at Madrid to celebrate the four
                    hundredth anniversary of the discovery of America, has been received and a copy
                    of it has been communicated to the Senate Committee on the Centennial of the
                    Constitution and the Discovery of America for their information.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
